definition.value: Lesbians employed as sex workers or otherwise engaged in sex work.
Bisexual persons employed as sex workers or otherwise engaged in sex work.
A person who dances, usually as a job or profession.
A person who has some association with religion in some sense, including those that refrain from religion (atheists and agnostics, among others).
Children whose parents have any of various LGBTQIA+ identities.
A form of hormone therapy in which estrogen hormones are replaced.
Sex as determined by hormone levels, typically gonadocorticoids such as androgens, estrogens, and progestogens (depending on the organism in question).

It is important to note that such designations are often based on "normal" ranges for "male" and "female", but it is not uncommon for these ranges to overlap or for individuals who are cisgender to have ranges more common for a different gender than their own. For this reason, individual level readings are preferable when providing such a designation.
A glossary of terms related to BDSM and/or BDSM culture.
A glossary of terms related to polyamory and/or polyamory culture.
A melanoma that arises usually from the breast skin and less often from the breast glandular tissue. Primary breast melanomas are rare.
A medieval and early modern monarchy in Western Europe. It was among the most powerful states in Europe and a great power since the Late Middle Ages and the Hundred Years' War.

A republic founded on 22 September 1792 during the French Revolution. The First Republic lasted until the declaration of the First Empire in 1804 under Napoleon, although the form of the government changed several times. This period was characterized by the fall of the monarchy, the establishment of the National Convention and the Reign of Terror, the Thermidorian Reaction and the founding of the Directory, and, finally, the creation of the Consulate and Napoleon's rise to power.
Slang that is specific to, or primarily used within, the Latine lesbian community.
Any of various political ideologies which focus upon sexuality-specific identities.
The sexual political philosophies of Michel Foucault, characterized primarily by the escape of the "confessional" structure of sexuality.
A gay male subculture consisting of gay men who self-identify as "chubs" and those that pursue them in sexual and/or romantic relationships ("chubby chasers").
A gay male subculture of persons who self-identify as bears, i.e. gay men with abundant body/facial hair and large builds.
Oppression caused by the arrangement of society benefitting a group at the expense of another.
Slang that is specific to, or primarily used within, the Latino gay male community.
Any of various communities associated with the leather subculture.
A clear or white discharge from the vagina, consisting mainly of mucus.
Any of various sexual interactions in which two or more people, or a person and a virtual character or characters, gather together via some communicatoin format and sexually arouse one another.
Virtual sex in the form of speech over telephone.
Virtual sex interactions via any written form of communication, such as letters or text messages.
Any of various virtual sexual interactions performed via computer.
Virtual sex interactions accomplished via the internet or some other computer network.
Any of various virtual sex activites accomplished via a virtual reality headset or virtual reality in general.
Technology which allows for remote mutual masturbation. Such systems communicate tactile sensations over a data link between participants.
Mutual masturbation assisted by teledildonic devices.
A lesion which occurs as the result of mechanical trauma.
An unnatural tract or ulcer.
A small tear in the thin, moist tissue (mucosa) that lines the anus. It appears as a crack or slit in the mucous membrane of the anus.
A consumer product used for personal hygiene or for beautification.

Substances intended to be applied to the human body for cleansing, beautifying, promoting attractiveness, or altering the appearance without affecting the body's structure or functions. Included in this definition are skin creams, lotions, perfumes, lipsticks, fingernail polishes, eye and facial makeup preparations, permanent waves, hair colors, toothpastes, and deodorants, as well as any material intended for use as a component of a cosmetic product.
Any of various cosmetics that are applied to the face to enhance one's appearance.
Any of various makeup products applied to the face.
Any of various makeup products applied to the area of the face around the eye, the eyelashes, or the eyebrows.
Any of various makeup products applied to the lips.
Any of various makeup products applied to the cheeks.
A cosmetic product used to define and line the eyes.
A cosmetic product applied on the eyelids and under the eyes to add depth and dimension, complement their color, make them appear larger, or to simply draw attention to them.
A cosmetic product applied to the lips for color, texture, and/or protection.
A cosmetic product used primarily to give the lips a glossy luster or to add a subtle color to them.
A cosmetic substance used on the eyelashes.
A system which centers upon and naturalizes heterosexuality, a binary gender system, and on maleness being ascribed more value than femaleness.
A condition in which an animal displays physical characteristics which are female and male, in varying proportions.
Gynandromorphism in which one half of the organism's body is female and the other half is male.
Phantom pain which mimics menstrual cramping.
Phantom menstrual pains may occur in post-menopausal women, in transgender men, and in persons who have had hysterectomies.
A marriage performed, recorded and recognized by a government official. Such a marriage may be performed by a religious body and recognised by the state, or it may be entirely secular.
The minimum age at which a person is allowed by law to marry, either as a right or subject to parental, judicial or other forms of approval.
